caption.text:
Summary of worst-case guarantees for the considered multiwinner rules. The definitions of the rules listed in the table are provided in Section
2
. The guarantees are functions of the committee size
k
. A higher value means a better guarantee, with 1 denoting optimal performance. In most cases we could only find (accurate) estimates instead of the exact values of the guarantees: the “lower” and “upper” values in the table denote that the respective guarantee is between these two bounds. The guarantees for the
p
-Geometric rule are visualized in
Fig. 1
(page 10). The column “Pareto” indicates whether the rule satisfies the Pareto efficiency axiom as discussed in Section
6
.
